{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"extension","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VisibleNode","preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode"]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Extended Enumeration","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VisibleNode"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO","kind":"identifier","text":"VisibleNode"}],"symbolKind":"extension","title":"VisibleNode","modules":[{"name":"ChromaShell","relatedModules":["ScribeCore"]}],"extendedModule":"ScribeCore","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:e:s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO11ChromaShellE04drawC0ySS_AD8ConsumedVtSi_SitF"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell","doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode\/drawVisible(_:_:)"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"references":{"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell","title":"ChromaShell","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A package to add more Chroma to your Swift terminal life.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell","kind":"symbol"},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore","title":"ScribeCore","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore"},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore/VisibleNode/drawVisible(_:_:)":{"title":"drawVisible(_:_:)","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode\/drawvisible(_:_:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"drawVisible"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> ("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11ChromaShell10ANSIStringa","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"ANSIString"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:11ChromaShell8ConsumedV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Consumed"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"abstract":[{"text":"A this point we can assume that all or most of the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"passed to us Almost fit into the height and width we have provided. The","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"job of this function is to tile or materialize the nodes into ASCII","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"escape codes.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The following assumptions are being made for now. This is currently","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"serving as the outline for what I would like the algorithm to be. But","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as there isn’t something I know a lot about how to do correctly or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"really know the best way to achieve this.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Scribe grantees something to be visual selected. This might sound"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"strange to some of you but if you think of your mouse or finger before"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you actually click this is sort of a way of selecting. Obviously those"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"examples are more complicated and I have ideas to work on them in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"future but best to start with the simplest example which I think is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the terminal and ASCII escape codes. Now It may be best to traverse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the tree to the selected node and then “tile” out from there as I would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"like to keep that element in the center of the screen give or take some"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"margin. Kinda to reflect similar behavior of vim letting you pad the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bottom of the text file."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The Next assumption is that text is to generally be centered in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"middle of the screen for now. Soon after I debug this algorithm I plan"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to surface apis for suggesting the text to be left or right, top or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"bottom. But I think a nice default is for the text to be centered."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"I haven’t really thought how to handle clipping or word wrapping yet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For now I think it’s best to just clip the text and allow the user to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pan around the graph. Which will mean I need to extend the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode"},{"type":"text","text":" type to allow deeper selections with in lines\/ words"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This will also be needed to visualize selecting charters of a word in a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text editor which I am to build with this UI\/UX framework."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"I guess the last thing I should mentioned is text should consume the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"amount of space possible. Until the size of all nodes is know and we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"know how much space to fill in around the information needing to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"displayed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Hopefully this helps other developers understanding what is going on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"here or at least future Zane. I have a somewhat working example of what"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"i’m trying to do in the ScribeModel repo. But I made different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"assumptions about the AST there so the problem is just different enough"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"here but it is possible."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode\/drawVisible(_:_:)","kind":"symbol"},"doc://ChromaShell/documentation/ChromaShell/ScribeCore/VisibleNode":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ChromaShell\/documentation\/ChromaShell\/ScribeCore\/VisibleNode","url":"\/documentation\/chromashell\/scribecore\/visiblenode","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VisibleNode"}],"abstract":[],"title":"VisibleNode","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10ScribeCore11VisibleNodeO","text":"VisibleNode"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"}}}